How to come up with a business name

Follow these steps to find a business name for your brand, and use our free Business Name Generator to get company name ideas.

Start Now

  1. Reflect on your values
    To build a strong brand, it’s important to choose a name that shows who you are as a company, what you stand for, and what you hope to achieve in the future.

  2. Know your audience
    Understanding your audience will help you to come up with a name that resonates, but also to build meaningful relationships and market your business effectively.

  3. Study the competition
    Scope out your competitors in order to spot trends in your industry and figure out what makes your business different from the rest—so you can pick a name that stands out.

  4. Plan for the future
    The name you choose should stay relevant as your business grows. Including a product type or location in your business name could impact your plans to expand down the line.

  5. Check name availability
    Once you’ve narrowed down your name options, conduct a Google search to see if other businesses are using them, and check whether the domain and social media handles are available.

  6. Test your business name
    Share your new name with potential customers and get their feedback. It can also be helpful to create mockups of your logo, website or packaging to see how the name looks.

Catchy business name ideas to inspire you

The best company names capture the essence of the brand, and the attention of their target audience. As you go through the process of choosing your business name, keep in mind that it should be simple and clear. If it’s easy for people to spell and pronounce, it will be easier to remember.

​

You also want a name that is unique to set you apart from the competition—the more original, the better. Find a memorable name that can stand the test of time and evolve with your long-term branding vision.

Company name generator FAQ

What is a business name generator?

A business name generator is an AI-powered tool that generates fresh and creative names for your business. By entering content related to your field, brand or vision, the AI generator uses an algorithm to suggest relevant and available names. The aim is to save you time, spark creativity and ensure you find a name that stands out. Many business generators, such as Wix’s, can also check domain availability so you can easily secure a website address that matches your brand.

How does the Business Name Generator work?

To use the brand name maker just follow these four simple steps:

  1. Enter a short description of your business. For example, if you have your own line of soap, enter a description like, “selling handmade soap made from organic materials.”

  2. Click Generate Names

  3. Create a free Wix account

  4. Answer a few additional questions about your brand, or skip straight to generating


Now you’ve got an impressive bunch of unique business names to choose from.

How much does the Business Name Generator cost?

There is no cost for you to use it. You can use the free Business Name Generator to create as many names as you want without any limitations.

How do I find creative business names?

Finding a creative business name for your brand is often a long process of brainstorming, researching and strategizing. But with a brand name generator the whole process is simplified. Just enter a short description about your business, answer one or two follow-up questions, and out comes a list of creative and catchy names.


You can also brainstorm clever names on your own by considering a variety of methods such as:

  • Alliteration

  • Abbreviations

  • Puns

  • Rhymes

  • Acronyms

  • Symbolism

How do I choose a good business name?

A good business name should be unique from your competitors and express what your business and brand stand for. Keep these tips in mind while choosing:

  • Think long term - Choose a name that gives your brand room to grow, otherwise you’ll run the risk of getting pigeonholed. In the future, you may want to expand your offerings or reach out to different sectors, so try to avoid picking a name that restricts you to a single product or audience.

  • Keep it simple - Go with a name that’s pronounceable and easy to spell. This will prevent any confusion or mixups and will help potential customers find your business faster when they search for it online.

  • Check availability - Make sure the name you like is still available for use. And if it is, register the domain quickly before someone else grabs it. The last thing you want is to spend your time creating the perfect name only to find out you can’t use it.

How can I know if a business name is taken?

There are several ways to find out if a business name is available:

  • Check the registry - Visit your country’s business registry website to get a list of all registered business names. For the U.S., check the official patent and trademark office at https://tmsearch.uspto.gov/search/search-information

  • Search on Google - Conduct a simple Google search to see if the name you want is already in use. It’s possible someone has taken the name even if it hasn’t been registered yet.

  • Go on social media - Look up the name on social platforms like Instagram, Twitter, Facebook and LinkedIn to ensure it’s not already taken.

  • Do a domain search - Use a tool like Wix’s domain name search to check if the name you want is available as a website URL.

Should I consider funny business names?

Funny business names shouldn’t be at the top of your list. They don’t really convey a sense of professionalism. However, this will be somewhat dependent on the industry you're looking to enter. Try and play around with words that have double meanings to convey a sense of fun.

What type of businesses use cool business names?

This can be somewhat subjective. In general, businesses that are trying to target a younger demographic try to pick names that their audience will think are cool and modern. Do some research on your target audience and see what type of language they use and what they will connect with.

How long should a business name be?

It’s generally a good idea to keep your business name short and sweet—no more than three words max. A name that’s too long won’t stand and potential customers may easily forget it. Shorter names also look cleaner when it comes to logos and branding.

What is the best business name generator?

As you consider which business name generator is best for you, keep the following key factors in mind:

  • Ease of use: An ideal name generator balances AI assistance with user-friendly steps, so you can find the perfect name quickly and intuitively.

  • Tailored searches: Generators like Wix’s ask follow-up questions based on your initial input to give you the most relevant names possible.

  • Domain checks: Wix not only suggests company names, but also checks domain availability, adding a higher level of efficiency to the process.

  • Path to business creation: With a platform like Wix, you can find a name, then continue straight to building your site and setting your business in motion—all from a single dashboard.
